        "Title": "Censored - an alaysis of cuts made to the film for its 1955 U.S. release",
        "Type": "Featurette",
        "Description": "When The Wages of Fear was first shown on American screens in 1955, it was in a much shorter form than the original French version. It is widely believed that the distributor made cuts -- eliminating perceived anti-Americanism and suggestions of homosexuality -- to appease U.S. sensibilities at the time. Following are scenes deleted from the U.S. version, as well as excerpts from articles discussing the cuts.",
